/boot    => kernel + GRUP (Boot files),    if you delete the gup, the system will work until you restart it

/etc    => Configuration Files for (Apps, Services, Users)

/home    => Users Directory

/root    => root directory

/bin    => contains Comands for Normal users

/sbin    => contain Admin Commands

/proc    => Contain all Runinng processes ID  

/dev    => Hardware Files  "Everything in Linux is a File, Including Hardware a,d Directories".

/usr    => Contain Installed "Apps and Services".





